  "why": "Although DeepXplore explicitly uses multiple independently-trained DNNs as cross-referencing oracles during fuzzing (i.e., differential testing) and its generation objective explicitly maximizes differences between models, the paper does not perform nor report any post-hoc experiments that take fault-inducing inputs discovered on one model (or a surrogate) and apply them to separate, previously unseen target models to measure transferability. The design therefore uses multi-model disagreement as an oracle during test generation (not as a surrogate-based attack transfer evaluation), and no section of the paper demonstrates reusing inputs crafted against one model on an unseen target.",
